## 4. Core Data Flows

### Flow 1: Document Upload Pipeline

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend
    participant FastAPI
    participant PyPDF2
    participant Chunker
    participant Gemini_Embed
    participant PostgreSQL

    User->>Frontend: Select PDF file
    Frontend->>FastAPI: POST /documents/upload (multipart)
    FastAPI->>FastAPI: Validate file is PDF
    FastAPI->>PyPDF2: Extract text from all pages
    PyPDF2-->>FastAPI: Raw text string
    FastAPI->>PostgreSQL: INSERT document metadata (filename, user_id)
    FastAPI->>Chunker: Split text into ~500 word chunks (50 word overlap)
    Chunker-->>FastAPI: List of text chunks
    
    loop For each chunk
        FastAPI->>Gemini_Embed: POST embedContent (chunk text)
        Gemini_Embed-->>FastAPI: 768-dimensional float vector
        FastAPI->>PostgreSQL: INSERT embedding (chunk_text, vector, user_id, doc_id)
        Note over PostgreSQL: Trigger auto-generates tsvector for BM25
    end
    
    FastAPI-->>Frontend: DocumentResponse (id, filename, created_at)
    Frontend-->>User: "Upload successful" notification
```

**What happens at each step:**

| Step | Component | Action | Output |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | User | Selects a PDF file | File bytes |
| 2 | FastAPI | Validates [.pdf](file:///d:/GenAI%20project/KnowBase%20AI%20%E2%80%93%20Multi-Tenant%20RAG%20SaaS%20Platform/backend/test_dummy.pdf) extension | Pass/fail |
| 3 | PyPDF2 | Reads every page, extracts text | Raw string |
| 4 | Chunker | Splits into 500-word chunks with 50-word overlap | List of chunks |
| 5 | Gemini API | Converts each chunk to 768-dim vector | Float array |
| 6 | PostgreSQL | Stores chunk text + vector + user_id | Embedding rows |
| 7 | DB Trigger | Auto-generates `tsvector` for BM25 search | tsvector column |

### Flow 2: Hybrid Search (BM25 + Vector + RRF)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Query
    participant Gemini_Embed
    participant PGVector
    participant PostgreSQL_FTS
    participant RRF

    Query->>Gemini_Embed: Convert question to 768-dim vector
    
    par Parallel Search
        Gemini_Embed->>PGVector: Cosine similarity search (semantic)
        PGVector-->>RRF: Top 15 chunks ranked by vector distance
    and
        Query->>PostgreSQL_FTS: Full-text search with plainto_tsquery
        PostgreSQL_FTS-->>RRF: Top 15 chunks ranked by BM25 score
    end
    
    RRF->>RRF: Reciprocal Rank Fusion (k=60)
    Note over RRF: RRF Score = 0.7 * 1/(60+vector_rank) + 0.3 * 1/(60+keyword_rank)
    RRF-->>Query: Top 5 chunks sorted by RRF score
```

**Why Hybrid is better than Vector-only:**

| Query | Vector Search Finds | BM25 Finds | Hybrid Finds |
|---|---|---|---|
| "Q3 revenue" | "financial performance", "quarterly results" | Exact match: "Q3", "revenue" | Both semantic + exact |
| "John Smith CEO" | "company leadership" | Exact: "John Smith", "CEO" | Perfect match |
| "explain the architecture" | Semantic matches about "system design" | Keyword: "architecture" | Comprehensive results |

### Flow 3: Streaming Chat (SSE)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Browser
    participant FastAPI
    participant HybridSearch
    participant Gemini_LLM
    participant Database

    User->>Browser: Types question, clicks Send
    Browser->>FastAPI: POST /chat/stream { query: "..." }
    FastAPI->>FastAPI: Validate JWT token
    FastAPI->>HybridSearch: Retrieve top 5 chunks (BM25 + Vector)
    HybridSearch-->>FastAPI: Context string with sources
    
    FastAPI->>Gemini_LLM: generate_content_stream(prompt)
    
    loop Token by token
        Gemini_LLM-->>FastAPI: Next text chunk
        FastAPI-->>Browser: SSE: data: {"token": "chunk"}
        Browser->>Browser: Append token to message UI
    end
    
    FastAPI->>Database: INSERT chat (query, full_response)
    FastAPI-->>Browser: SSE: data: {"done": true, "chat_id": "uuid"}
    User->>Browser: Reads complete, formatted answer
```

**SSE Event Format:**
```
data: {"token": "Based"}

data: {"token": " on"}

data: {"token": " your"}

data: {"token": " documents"}

...

data: {"done": true, "chat_id": "a1b2c3d4-..."}
```

### Flow 4: RAG Evaluation (RAGAS)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin
    participant FastAPI
    participant RAG_Pipeline
    participant RAGAS
    participant Gemini_Eval

    Admin->>FastAPI: POST /eval/run
    
    loop For each test question (5 samples)
        FastAPI->>RAG_Pipeline: Retrieve context for question
        RAG_Pipeline-->>FastAPI: Retrieved chunks
        FastAPI->>RAG_Pipeline: Generate LLM answer
        RAG_Pipeline-->>FastAPI: Generated answer
    end
    
    FastAPI->>RAGAS: Evaluate (questions, answers, contexts, ground_truths)
    RAGAS->>Gemini_Eval: Judge context precision
    RAGAS->>Gemini_Eval: Judge context recall
    RAGAS->>Gemini_Eval: Judge faithfulness
    RAGAS->>Gemini_Eval: Judge answer relevance
    Gemini_Eval-->>RAGAS: Scores (0.0 - 1.0)
    RAGAS-->>FastAPI: EvalResult with 4 metric scores
    
    FastAPI-->>Admin: JSON with scores + details + interpretation
```

