## 10. Environment Configuration

### Backend ([backend/.env](file:///d:/GenAI%20project/KnowBase%20AI%20%E2%80%93%20Multi-Tenant%20RAG%20SaaS%20Platform/backend/.env))

```env
# ── Database ──
# PostgreSQL connection string (auto-converts postgres:// to postgresql+asyncpg://)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:password@localhost:5432/knowbase

# ── Authentication ──
JWT_SECRET=your-random-secret-string-here    # Used to sign JWT tokens
ALGORITHM=HS256                               # JWT signing algorithm
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=1440              # Token valid for 24 hours

# ── AI Services ──
GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSy...                      # Get from https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
```

### Frontend ([frontend/.env.local](file:///d:/GenAI%20project/KnowBase%20AI%20%E2%80%93%20Multi-Tenant%20RAG%20SaaS%20Platform/frontend/.env.local))

```env
# Backend API URL — must match where uvicorn listens
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **If accessing from another device (phone, another PC on LAN):**
> - Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://YOUR_PC_IP:8000`
> - Start uvicorn with `--host 0.0.0.0` to listen on all network interfaces

### Database Connection Pool Settings (in [session.py](file:///d:/GenAI%20project/KnowBase%20AI%20%E2%80%93%20Multi-Tenant%20RAG%20SaaS%20Platform/backend/app/db/session.py))

| Setting | Value | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `pool_pre_ping` | True | Validates connection before use (prevents stale connections) |
| `pool_recycle` | 300 | Recycle connections every 5 minutes |
| `pool_size` | 10 | Maximum persistent connections |
| `max_overflow` | 20 | Extra connections during traffic spikes |

---

## 11. Setup & Deployment

### Local Development Setup

#### Prerequisites
- Python 3.11+
- Node.js 18+
- PostgreSQL with PGVector extension (or Railway cloud DB)
- Google Gemini API key

#### Step 1: Backend Setup

```powershell
cd backend

# Create and activate virtual environment
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate        # Windows
# source venv/bin/activate   # Mac/Linux

# Install all dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Create .env file with your credentials
# (see Environment Configuration section above)
```

#### Step 2: Frontend Setup

```powershell
cd frontend

# Install Node dependencies
npm install

# Create .env.local
echo NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000 > .env.local
```

#### Step 3: Start Backend

```powershell
cd backend
venv\Scripts\activate
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

You should see:
```
INFO:     Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8000
INFO:     Application startup complete.
✅ BM25 full-text search infrastructure ready
```

#### Step 4: Start Frontend

```powershell
cd frontend
npm run dev
```

#### Step 5: Open Browser

Navigate to `http://localhost:3000` → Register → Upload a PDF → Chat!

### Docker Deployment

```powershell
# From the project root
docker-compose up --build
```

Services:
- [db](file:///d:/GenAI%20project/KnowBase%20AI%20%E2%80%93%20Multi-Tenant%20RAG%20SaaS%20Platform/backend/app/db/session.py#18-21) — PostgreSQL with PGVector (port 5432)
- `backend` — FastAPI (port 8000)
- `frontend` — Next.js (port 3000)

